last_episode_to_air.overview: Zoo vets treat seven pythons; orphaned otter pups go to fish school; and keepers rush to help Arctic foxes with mysterious injuries.

name: Secrets of the Zoo: North Carolina
original_name: Secrets of the Zoo: North Carolina
overview: North Carolina is home to the world's largest zoo, with 2,600 acres, large natural habitats and more than 1,800 animals in its care. The show features several Zoo staff, including keepers and veterinarians, and highlight stories, including routine animal husbandry, emergency procedures and the Zoo’s work in conservation and rescue and release of injured wildlife

episodes.name: Chimp Off the Old Block
episodes.overview: Zoo keepers prepare for a chimp birth, vets investigate a bear’s mystery illness and a dangerous antelope is darted on the zoo’s grasslands habitat.

episodes.name: Dr. Zoo-little
episodes.overview: A gorilla has emergency dental surgery, vets examine a deadly rattlesnake and zoo keepers try to take blood from a lion’s tail.

episodes.name: Hiss and Hers
episodes.overview: Zookeepers prepare for the birth of a white rhino; two young lions leave the pride; and a pair of cannibalistic snakes go on some risky dates.

episodes.name: Polar Bear Opposites
episodes.overview: The zoo hopes for a polar-bear pregnancy; two endangered red wolves go on a blind date; and a young elephant gets some unusual treatment.

episodes.name: Giraffic Park
episodes.overview: The zoo welcomes a timid, new giraffe to the herd; a pregnant bat prepares to give birth; and devoted keepers give an epileptic chimp a better life.

episodes.name: Much Ado About Puffin
episodes.overview: The doctors at the North Carolina Zoo are swamped! A huge alligator, with a history of illness, needs blood drawn, and a ferocious lioness goes under the knife to remove a cracked tooth.

episodes.name: Puffin But Trouble
episodes.overview: Keepers hope for a long-awaited sand cat kitten, while a nervous puffin learns to swim.
